    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="604"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">647.116/182: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-27T10:00:00+10:00"
                            >June 27, 1936—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 27—6:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 24, 11 a.m. I have just received a 400-word reply to my note of June
                    6th. This reiterates Australia’s inability any longer “to <pb facs="0843"
                        n="763" xml:id="pg_763"/> accept with equanimity the heavy disequilibrium in
                    the trade of the Commonwealth with the United States” with the resulting
                    decision “to check imports from those countries which find it impossible to
                    trade on a reasonable basis of [practical] reciprocity.”</p>
                <p>The key sentence reads: “Collectors of Customs in declining to issue permits for
                    the importation of these commodities are acting under instructions and in
                    accordance with the policy of the Government.”</p>
                <p>Text by air mail.<note n="20" xml:id="d604fn20">Enclosure to despatch No. 238,
                        June 27, 1936; not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moffat</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
